BRIEFLY 
Lowes Hotels, Covia Join on Project: Lowes Hotels and Covia said they intended 
to form a joint venture called C/LAS (for Covia/Loews Automated Services) that 
would sell computer reservation systems to small- and medium-sized hotels. 
Terms of the transaction weren't disclosed. Covia, owned by a partnership of 
six foreign and domestic airlines, including United Airlines, operates the 
Apollo airline travel reservation system. Lowes, through a subsidiary, sells 
marketing and reservation services to 400 hotel clients. 
